$ Shell command: tail
@ tail

{ -f #tail-f

`tail -f fileName` comes in especially handy when a log file that is being written to needs to be monitored: as soon as a new line is appended to the log file, `tail -f` will print it to
STDOUT.

code {
$ tail -f logFile
code }

  → development/tools/scripts/personal/highlight_pl is a perl script that can be used as a template for highlighting words (such as ERROR or WARNING).

